      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add Neuralwatt provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCodexBar can now track Neuralwatt account credit exhaustion from the official quota API. Neuralwatt behaves like DeepSeek-style prepaid credits: the balance depletes until topped up, so the menu surfaces the dollar balance without reset language or subscription renewal dates.\n\nThis also wires Neuralwatt through provider settings, config/env API-key resolution, token-account selection, CLI/provider docs, widget exhaustiveness, and provider reference docs.\n\n## Details\n\n- Adds `neuralwatt` as a provider ID with API-key auth against `GET /v1/quota`.\n- Displays the primary USD credit balance as non-resetting status text.\n- Supports optional per-key spending allowance windows when the quota response includes an allowance.\n- Rejects malformed successful quota responses instead of rendering fake `$0.00` balances.\n- Marks known zero-credit balances as exhausted instead of healthy.\n- Handles fractional ISO8601 subscription timestamps defensively, even though subscription periods are not rendered as resets.\n\n## Redacted runtime proof\n\nA local CodexBar CLI fetch against a configured Neuralwatt API key successfully returned usage from the live API. Private amounts and timestamps are redacted:\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"provider\": \"neuralwatt\",\n    \"source\": \"api\",\n    \"usage\": {\n      \"identity\": {\n        \"loginMethod\": \"Energy\",\n        \"providerID\": \"neuralwatt\"\n      },\n      \"loginMethod\": \"Energy\",\n      \"primary\": {\n        \"resetDescription\": \"<redacted balance detail>\",\n        \"usedPercent\": \"<number>\"\n      },\n      \"secondary\": null,\n      \"tertiary\": null,\n      \"updatedAt\": \"<redacted timestamp>\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n```\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift build`\n- Focused Neuralwatt usage-fetcher tests — 10 passing tests\n- Focused Neuralwatt menu-card tests — 1 passing test\n- `swift test --filter ProviderEnvironmentResolverTests` — 6 passing tests\n- `swift test --filter ProviderConfigEnvironmentTests` — 36 passing tests\n- `swift test --filter CLIConfigCommandTests` — 12 passing tests\n- `swift test --filter ConfigurationDocsProviderIDTests` — 1 passing test\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n\nFull `make test` was not used as the final gate because it times out in this headless local environment; focused Swift tests and build pass.\n\n---\n\n[![Compound Engineering](https://img.shields.io/badge/Built_with-Compound_Engineering-6366f1)](https://github.com/EveryInc/compound-engineering-plugin)\n![Pi](https://img.shields.io/badge/Pi-000000)",
